page.title: 14GENERAL SURVEY
page.content:
With the exception of the three square kilometres along the western edge, the block is almost entirely composed of {livestock}farming country, with a little woodland. This is mainly deciduous and not commercially managed. The western part is, for the most part, devoted to{commercial fruit {and vegetable growing.}
The{Hartlebury Trading Estate}is devoted mainly to light industry and storage and there are large{grain} stores there. The only village in the block is{Cutnall Green.}This is quite a small village and most of the inhabitants{commute}to nearby towns for employment.
